data.description:
Anastasia always forget her birthday ! She'd like to know when (which date) and when (in how many days) what age she'll be. . .

She also like to know same things about her friends (even if for some of them she doesn't know their year of birth).

Can you help ?

## The Job
You'll have to build a `Birthday` object to handle the birthday of a person:

```javascript
new Birthday( name, day, month [, year] )
```
* `name` is a string,
* `day`, `month`, `year` are integers
  - `day` from 1 to 31,
  - `month` from 1 (not 0) to 12
  - `year` (if provided) over 1500

`Birthday` instances have 4 methods :

```javascript
Birthday#next() // -> returns date of "next" birthday
  //...'date' is a Date instance
  //!\ if birthday is "today" return today date !

Birthday#age() // -> returns age of the person on next birthday
  //...'age' is an integer
  //!\ if no year was provided to the constructor returns 'undefined'

Birthday#days() // -> returns number of days until next birthday
  //...if birthday is "today" number of days == 0 !

Birthday#toString() // -> returns a string of the form :
  // "Name was born on Www Mmm DD YYYY", where :
  // - Name is name of the person
  // - Www is name of the day of the week (3 chars)
  // - Mmm is name of the month (3 chars)
  // - DD is the day of the month (2 digits)
  // - YYYY is the year (4 digits) if provided to the constructor
  // If no year was provided the string will be :
  // "Name was born on Mmm DD"
```

For the purpose of the tests "today" will be arbitrarily fixed and will change along the tests. You'll may (and probably you'll **have to**) use the var `TODAY` to get the currently "today" value.

###  Examples

```javascript
var kat = new Birthday("Katya",2,5,1729);

kat.toString()  // -> "Katya was born on Mon May 02 1729"

TODAY = new Date(2015,6,1);
kat.next()  // -> Mon May 02 2016 00:00:00 GMT+0200
kat.age()   // -> 287 (woah!)

TODAY = new Date(2015,3,23)
kat.days() // -> 10
TODAY = new Date(2015,4,1)
kat.days() // -> 1
TODAY = new Date(2015,4,2)
kat.days() // -> 0
kat.next() // -> Sat May 02 2015 00:00:00 GMT+0200
```

**Note** : You don't have to change `TODAY`, tests do it. `TODAY` should be used every time you would call `new Date()` (without argument) in normal conditions to get the date of the the day.
